festival.introText:
Manchester Psyche Fest returns for 2023!

 

Bringing the Manchester psychedelic community together.

 

Line-up

Over 60 live acts:

The Brian Jonestown Massacre

Los Bitchos. Sorry. The Lovely Eggs.

Ulrika Spacek. Crocodiles. The Underground Youth.

Panic Shack. White Flowers. L'Eclair.

Jemima Coulter. Maruja. Regressive Left. Heartworms.

Madmadmad. Sun Fruits. Cruush.

+ headliners & many more TBA.

 

Where

Multi-venue festival at Albert Hall, o2 Ritz, Canvas, Gorilla, YES, Deaf Institute.

Ticket gains access to all venues. ***

When

Saturday 2nd September 2023.

 

Art

Exhibitions, murals, workshops & visuals to be announced.

 

Food Stalls

Street food will be available across the festival catering for all dietary requirements.

 

Tickets

Limited £40* early bird tickets from 10am 9th Dec

 

Wristband Collection x Festival Hub

Info coming soon.

 

Ages

14+ (before 11pm) Albert Hall, o2 Ritz , Canvas, Gorilla & Deaf Institute

18+ YES, all venues after 11pm

 

NB:

Line-up subject to change.

Venue capacities are based on first come first serve so please arrive early for specific acts.

Each venue have their own T&C’s – please refer to their websites for detailed info.

*Plus booking fees.

reviews.title: Review of Manchester Psych Fest 2019
reviews.body: Huge improvement on last year, pity the Ritz closed so early, but Yes took up the slack with some great bands and DJ's. Looking forward to next year already!

reviews.title: Review of Manchester Psych Fest 2019
reviews.body:
I do like the concept of the event is spread over several venues, keep it going in my opinion.

I was only surprised so the fact so many attendees were smokers, so I was caught in the cloud of second smoke waiting outside the Gorilla for Pigs (is 6x). Say a big thank you, security staff, in managing all the people traffic smokers and drunks with such good humor.

reviews.title: Review of Manchester Psych Fest 2019
reviews.body: Much improved venues from last year. Well attended and great atmosphere. Lovely Eggs and MaidaVale smashed it!!

reviews.title: Review of Manchester Psych Fest 2017
reviews.body:
Great to stray...
A variety of bands to try out across the three venues; if something did not float your boat then you just changed your venue.
Impossible to see all the bands but some highlights (mine!) were Freakout Honey's vocals and grooves, Pink Kink's enthusiasm & set, (...the crazy and limitless world of...) Mother; Ryley Walker's hypnotic folk guitar and a precise finale by Teleman.
Everything in place then for another (BIGGER) Psyche Fest in 2018!

SJM.

reviews.title: Review of Manchester Psych Fest 2017
reviews.body: Great day! Excellent bands, good venues and well organised

faqs.question: When is Manchester Psych Fest 2023?
faqs.answer: Manchester Psych Fest returns to the city on Saturday the 2nd and Sunday the 3rd of September 2023.

faqs.question: How do I get to Manchester Psych Fest?
Does Manchester Psych Fest have onsite camping?
faqs.answer: No, Manchester Psych Fest does not have any camping available as it is a one day festival.

faqs.question: What happens if I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer: Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent. Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: Where is Manchester Psych Fest?
faqs.answer: Manchester Psyche Fest is a multi-venue festival - venues TBC
